definitions.definition: A set of structured activities ; a plan of action.
examples: Our program for today’s exercise class includes swimming and jogging.

definitions.definition: A leaflet listing information about a play, game or other activity.
examples: The program consisted of ads for restaurants and the credits of everyone connected with the play.

definitions.definition: A set of principal goals which someone, especially a political party or candidate, supports.
A performance of a show or other broadcast on radio or television .
examples: Tonight’s program was hosted by Johnny Carson.
The program runs on both Linux and Microsoft Windows .

definitions.definition: A particular mindset or method of doing things.
labels: especially in the phrase " get with the program "
definitions.label_groups: especially in the phrase " get with the program "
